modules.description: Processes and manipulates semantic version constraints, supporting parsing from and formatting to string representations. Operates on version ranges that specify exact, minor, or patch version requirements. Useful for version comparison logic in package management or dependency resolution workflows.

This module implements semantic versioning operations for comparing, incrementing, and parsing three-part version numbers (major, minor, patch). It supports exact comparisons, version bumps, and string conversion, with a sub-module for evaluating version constraints against lists of available versions. It is used to implement package version selection and dependency resolution logic.
